Package RRPSS

Class Order

Object
Order
public class Order extends Object
Contains the information of order created by the system that is stored in the order database. Each order contains a list of menu items and promotional items.
Since:
2021-11-03
Version:
1.0
Author:
Chua Chong Yih

    • Order

      public Order​(String staffName, boolean member, int pax, int orderNumber, int tableNum)
      Creates a new order with the given parameter. Sets the LocalDateTime as the time this order was created.
      Parameters:
      staffName - The name of the staff assigned to this order.
      member - The membership status of the customer of this order.
      pax - The number of customers in this order.
      orderNumber - The order number of this order assigned by the database
      table - The table assigned to this order.

  • Method Details

    • addOrderItem

      public void addOrderItem​(MenuItem m)
      Adds a new menu item into the orderItem list. Sorts the orderItem list in order of the name of item. Adds the price of the menu item to the total price of this order.
      Parameters:
      m - The menu item to be added to the orderItem list.

    • removeOrderItem

      public void removeOrderItem​(MenuItem m)
      Removes the menu item from the orderItem list. Deducts the price of the menu item from the price of this order.
      Parameters:
      m - The menu item to be removed from the orderItem list.

    • findItem

      private int findItem​(MenuItem m)
      Search the order list for the matching menu item.
      Parameters:
      m - the menu item to be searched.
      Returns:
      the index of the menu item in the order list.

    • getAllClasses

      public ArrayList<Class<?>> getAllClasses()
      Finds all unique classes that are in the menu arraylist and stores it in an ArrayList.
      Returns:
      ArrayList of classes that are in the menu.

    • printOrderList

      public void printOrderList()
      Prints the list of menu and promotional items in this order. Prices listed are inclusive of GST. Members are entitled to 15% discount from the final price.

    • printOrderDetails

      public void printOrderDetails()
      Prints the list of menu and promotional items in this order. List of menu and promotional items are consolidated such that the same types of items are displayed in a single row with the amount of repeated items. Prices listed are inclusive of GST. Members are entitled to 15% discount from the final price.
